"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828730","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-29","<p>Since 2008, the Ministry of Defence has entered into more than 70 contracts with the Chemring group. These are for a range of services. I am withholding further details as disclosure would prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-01-29T16:23:50.29Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828730/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828730/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828730/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-23","Ministry of Defence: Chemring Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will list the contracts that his Department has entered into with Chemring and its subsidiaries in each of the past 10 years.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","124375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828731","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-31","<p>The Department for Work &amp; Pensions employed 252 Pension Credit claims staff and 302 Carer’s Allowance claims staff in December 2017. This is the latest information held by the Department. This compares with 287 Pension Credit claims staff and 190 Carer’s Allowance claims staff in January 2017.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-01-31T11:17:17.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828731/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828731/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-23","Department for Work and Pensions: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many staff are currently employed in her Department to administer pension credit and carer's allowance claims; and how those figures compare with the number of those employed in January 2017.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","124376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828733","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-29","<p>To improve quality of care, the Department and NHS England are transforming mental health service provision to provide equitable access to high quality care for all people, including transgender people. Local areas are required to consider their local population’s needs, including access to services based on clinical need, when they commission and provide services and support.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is investing an additional £1 billion by 2020 to deliver a major expansion of mental health services, including liaison psychiatry in every accident and emergency department, putting crisis resolution and home treatment teams on 24/7 footing and expanding perinatal mental health services.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-01-29T16:44:27.163Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828733/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828733/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828733/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-23","Mental Health Services: Gender Recognition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans his Department has to improve mental health provision for transgender people.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","124377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828734","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-29","<p>From February 2018, the seven-day waiting period will be removed for all new Universal Credit claimants. This means that no claimant should wait longer than five weeks to receive their first Universal Credit payment.</p><p>DWP has also improved the Universal Credit advances process. Claimants who require support can now get an advance of up to 100 per cent of their expected monthly entitlement while they wait for their first payment. This effectively removes the wait until their first payment altogether.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-01-29T15:00:58.76Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828734/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828734/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828734/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-23","Universal Credit: Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps her Department has taken to reduce the time taken to make payments of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","124378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828735","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-31","<p>The Secretary of State, in his previous role as Minister for Digital, wrote to Mayor Andy Burnham on 22nd December 2017, responding to the Mayor’s request for more information on the government’s investment of £21m in Tech Nation. This funding involves setting up 10 new regional hubs, including in Manchester (which will serve as the base for the North West) to support and promote the needs of the local tech communities. The Secretary of State clarified that Tech nation will work with local partners to connect with and build on the networks and ecosystems that already exist. The Mayor has been introduced to senior Tech Nation staff who are assessing the unique needs of each region.</p><p> </p><p>This letter also offered further discussion with DCMS on how government policy can help to deliver the Greater Manchester Digital Strategy. I also committed to meeting Mr Burnham following our appearance on Question Time on 18th January 2018.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-01-31T17:31:10.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828735/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828735/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828735/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-23","Technology: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions he has had with the Mayor of Greater Manchester on promoting Greater Manchester's technology sector.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","124379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828736","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-02","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the statement made by my Rt. Hon Friend, the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, <a href="https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-01-23/debates/3BEE8BA3-B281-4853-A2F7-6F787417B61D/PersonalIndependencePayment" target="_blank">Official Report</a>, 23 January 2018, Column 139.</p><p>The Department will work with key stakeholders to implement the MH Upper Tribunal judgment.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","124381","2018-02-02T10:50:08.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828736/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828736/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828736/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-23","Personal Independence Payment: Mental Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Written Statement of 19 January 2018, HCWS414, on Welfare, when her Department plans to publish updated guidance for assessors to reflect that High Court ruling.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","124380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828737","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-02","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the statement made by my Rt. Hon Friend, the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, <a href="https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-01-23/debates/3BEE8BA3-B281-4853-A2F7-6F787417B61D/PersonalIndependencePayment" target="_blank">Official Report</a>, 23 January 2018, Column 139.</p><p>The Department will work with key stakeholders to implement the MH Upper Tribunal judgment.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","124380","2018-02-02T10:50:08.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828737/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828737/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828737/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-23","Personal Independence Payment: Mental Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Written Statement of 19 January 2018, HCWS414, on Welfare, when her Department plans to publish updated guidance for claimants to reflect that High Court ruling.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","124381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828738","Home Office","false","2018-01-25","<p>The Home Office is in regular correspondence with Police and Crime Commissioners on a range of topics, including funding and resources.</p><p>I recently announced the proposed police funding settlement for 2018/19 which would see an additional £450m invested in the policing system, around £270m direct to PCCs. Should the Mayor choose to use increased precept flexibility, this could mean an additional £10.4m for Greater Manchester Police. It is a matter for police leaders to determine locally how to use these resources.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick  Hurd",,"2018-01-25T15:03:23.723Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828738/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828738/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828738/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-23","Greater Manchester Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent representations she has received from the Mayor of Greater Manchester on changes (a) in the number of police officers and (b) to police funding.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","124382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828740","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-29","<p>The International Monetary Fund (IMF) is an independent international organisation. The official economy and fiscal forecasts produced by the Office for Budget Responsibility are used to inform policy decisions.</p><p> </p><p>The IMF recently concluded their Article IV assessment of the UK economy and judge that “The fiscal framework adopted by the authorities prudently aims to reduce the deficit (after accounting for the impact of the economic cycle) to below 2 percent of GDP by 2020/21, and to balance the budget by the middle of the next decade.”</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-01-29T16:10:01.317Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828740/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828740/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828740/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-23","Economic Growth","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the IMF's revision of the UK's growth outlook from 1.6 to 1.5 per cent for 2019.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","124383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828741","Department for Education","false","2018-01-31","<p>The government knows how important it is that children with medical conditions are supported to enjoy a full education. That is why it has introduced a new duty to require governing boards to make arrangements to support pupils with medical conditions, and have provided statutory guidance outlining schools’ responsibilities in this area. This guidance sets out that governing boards should ensure that all schools develop a policy for supporting pupils with medical conditions that is reviewed regularly and is readily accessible to parents and school staff. We keep the guidance under review, including in the context of school awareness, and the role it plays in securing accessibility of school policies</p><p>Ofsted’s Common Inspection Framework requires inspectors, in making judgements, to pay particular attention to the outcomes of a range of groups of pupils, including those with medical needs. Ofsted included guidance to inspectors on this matter in their March 2017 school inspection update, reminding inspectors that they should consider how schools are meeting the needs of pupils with medical conditions.</p><p>The department works with organisations such as the Health Conditions in Schools Alliance to help raise awareness of the duty on schools, and recently promoted the duty through the department’s social media channels.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","124400 ; 124404","2018-01-31T14:42:00.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828741/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828741/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828741/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-23","Pupils: Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that the medical conditions policies of schools are checked by Ofsted as part of their regular system of inspections.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","124384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828743","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-19","<p>The Minister for the Cabinet Office did not have any meetings with the Government Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The Government Chief Scientific Adviser regularly meets Ministers throughout Government.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2018-02-19T14:34:18.577Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828743/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828743/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828743/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-23","Government Chief Scientific Adviser","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many meetings he had with the Government’s Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","124385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828744","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-31","<p>The previous Secretary of State, David Lidington, did not meet with the Chief Scientific Advisor between October and December 2017.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-01-31T16:06:11.953Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828744/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828744/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828744/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-23","Ministry of Justice: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many meetings (a) he and (b) his predecessor had with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","124386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828745","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-01-30","<p>There have been no meetings with the Chief Scientific Adviser and the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland between October 2017 and December 2017.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-01-30T15:54:45.19Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828745/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828745/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828745/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-01-23","Northern Ireland Office: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many meetings (a) she and (b) her predecessor had with the Government Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","124387"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828747","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-02-01","<p>Between October and December 2017 the Secretary of State met Chris Jones, Chief Scientific Adviser at DExEU, five times. It should be noted that this is a dual role combined with the Director of Justice, Security and Migration position and conversations would have covered both briefs.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2018-02-01T11:04:36.583Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828747/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828747/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828747/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-01-23","Department for Exiting the European Union: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","124388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828748","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-31","<p>FCO Ministers have regular meetings with the Department's Chief Scientific Adviser, and his Deputy, most recently on 30 January 2018.</p><p> </p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-01-31T14:20:14.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828748/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828748/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828748/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-01-23","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many meetings he had with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","124389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828749","Prime Minister","false","2018-01-31","<p>I have regular meetings with ministerial colleagues, officials and others.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2018-01-31T16:09:49.193Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828749/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828749/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828749/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2018-01-23","Government Chief Scientific Adviser","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, how many meetings she had with the Government Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","124390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828751","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-30","<p>The Department for Transport Chief Scientific Adviser (CSA) met with the Secretary of State once during this period, with other senior officials. The CSA also met with the former Parliamentary under Secretary of State, Paul Maynard MP, and the Parliamentary under Secretary of State, Jesse Norman MP, during this time period.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-01-30T14:50:17.077Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828751/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828751/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828751/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-23","Department for Transport: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","124391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828752","Home Office","false","2018-01-30","<p>Home Office Ministers have regular meetings as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2018-01-30T15:58:11.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828752/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828752/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828752/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-23","Home Office: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many meetings she had with her Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","124392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828753","Department for International Trade","false","2018-02-01","<p>Dr Mike Short CBE has recently taken up his position as Chief Scientific Advisor at the Department for International Trade (DIT). My Rt. Hon Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade publicly welcomed his appointment when it was announced, stating how ‘Dr Short’s many decades of experience in technology, innovation and public policy will ensure that cutting-edge scientific and technical know-how is firmly at the core of DIT’s work’. The Secretary of State will be formally meeting Dr Short in the coming weeks.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-02-01T17:05:37.62Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828753/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828753/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828753/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-01-23","Department for International Trade: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","124393"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828754","Department for International Development","false","2018-02-01","<p>The Chief Scientific Adviser has met with the Secretary of State on 4 occasions within the time frame.</p><p>I hold the portfolio responsibility for DFID's Science and Research department. I have met the DFID Chief Scientific Adviser once since my appointment in January. In addition, DFID’s Chief Scientific Adviser has also had a meeting with DFID Lord Bates during this period.</p><p>The Chief Scientific Adviser met with my predecessor, Rory Stewart, on 3 occasions during the period of October – December 2017. The Deputy Chief Scientific Adviser also attended the Research Roundtable session with Minister Stewart.</p><p>The Chief Scientific Adviser continues to provide all Ministers with regular written submissions and briefings on DFID science and research activities.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-02-01T15:14:47.387Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828754/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828754/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-01-23","Department for International Development: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many meetings (a) she and (b) her predecessor had with her Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","124394"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828756","Scotland Office","false","2018-01-30","<p>I did not meet with the Government Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-01-30T15:49:43.233Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828756/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828756/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828756/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-01-23","Scotland Office: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many meetings he had with the Government Chief Scientific Adviser between October and December 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","124395"
