"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828925","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-29","<p>The Secretary of State for Health and Social Care has not received any representations from South Tyneside Council regarding the devolution of local health services to that local authority.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-01-29T12:39:20.89Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828925/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828925/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828925/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-23","Health Services: South Tyneside","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether he has received representations from South Tyneside Council on devolving local health services to that local authority; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","124534"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828926","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-29","<p>The Department has not currently received any representations from South Tyneside Council about devolving local health services.</p><p> </p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-01-29T14:03:09.927Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828926/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828926/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828926/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-23","South Tyneside Council: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether he has received representations from South Tyneside Council on devolving local health services to that local authority.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","124535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828928","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-29","<p>The data requested is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>The safety of mother and baby is paramount. We want to ensure that women have as many choices as possible, minimising any known risk to either themselves or their baby.</p><p> </p><p>Maternity services are unable to plan the exact time and place of birth and there are occasions when a unit cannot safely accept more women into their care. In such cases, the only safe alternative is to close the unit temporarily. It is important of course, that where a unit closes, there are systems and guidelines in place to ensure pregnant women have access to the next closest maternity unit and the type of care they have chosen, including midwifery-led care.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-01-29T17:05:30.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828928/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828928/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828928/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-23","Maternity Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many hospitals have had to close or temporarily suspend their (a) maternity wards and (b) Special Care Baby Units in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","124536"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828929","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-29","<p>Under licence conditions, energy suppliers must inform their customers prior to the installation of a smart meter that they may lose meter functionality when switching. In addition, before any switch is concluded, the new supplier must tell the consumer about any change in how their meter will operate and the service they will receive.</p><p> </p><p>These requirements aim to help consumers make informed decisions about switching, in the period before first generation smart meters are enrolled into the national data and communications platform and thus can be operated by any energy supplier.</p><p> </p><p>Second generation meters use the smart metering infrastructure run by the Data and Communications Company and will enable all consumers to retain their smart functionality when they switch supplier.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-01-29T16:52:11.747Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828929/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828929/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828929/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-23","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps are being taken to inform the general public about the limitations of first generation smart meters; and what plans he has to ensure that the roll-out of second generation meters removes those limitations.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","124537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828930","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-29","<p>The Office for Product Safety and Standards will have a budget of around £12 million per year to fund additional product safety activities, when it is fully operational.</p><p> </p><p>Initially, this new capacity will be funded through central Government but, longer-term, the Government will consider alternative funding options.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-01-29T15:46:28.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828930/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828930/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828930/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-23","Office for Product Safety and Standards: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what funding has been allocated from the public purse for the Office for Product Safety and Standards.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","124538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828931","Department for Education","false","2018-01-29","<p>Based on information supplied by local authorities, fourteen children’s centres have opened since April 2010.[1]</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1] The figure for centres opened since 2010 does not include children’s centres that local authorities have reported closed and subsequently reopened.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-01-29T17:23:43.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828931/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828931/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828931/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-23","Children's Centres","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 22 January 2018 to Question 123506, on Children's Centres: Closures, how many new children's centres have opened since 2010.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","124539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828932","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-29","<p>We have been as open as possible in sharing information subject to the overwhelming national interest of preserving our negotiating position, including publishing 14 detailed papers on the negotiations to date.</p><p> </p><p>Any non-public reports are by definition not shared with individuals and organisations outside government.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2018-01-29T09:30:14.1Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828932/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828932/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828932/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-01-23","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 23 January 2018 to Question 122410 on Brexit, whether any journalist has been given access to non-public Market Access reports pertaining to the UK’s withdrawal from the EU that did not undermine the UK's negotiating position.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","124540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828934","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-02-01","<p>Smoking related litter is considered to be litter and the Government has made no particular assessment of its environmental effect.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-02-01T14:15:13.653Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828934/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828934/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828934/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-01-23","Tobacco: Waste","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether his Department has made an assessment of the environmental effect of cigarette waste; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","124541"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828935","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-31","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy sets the overall budgets of the independent Research Councils and Innovate UK, which then allocate funds for individual grants and research organisations in line with the Haldane Principle.</p><p> </p><p>The Research Councils and Innovate UK have spent the following amounts on research and development in the field of biodegradable and compostable plastics in each of the last 15 years. Data older than 10 years may be less reliable. Further information on research and development projects can be found on the RCUK Gateway to Research, see: <a href="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk/" target="_blank">http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk</a>.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>Biotechnology and Biological Sciences Research Council (BBSRC)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Engineering and Physical Sciences Research Council (EPSRC)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Innovate UK</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td><td><p>£210,000</p></td><td><p>£4,644,293</p></td><td><p>£104,344</p></td><td><p><strong>£4,958,637</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p>£276,000</p></td><td><p>£3,663,120</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p><strong>£3,939,120</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p>£262,000</p></td><td><p>£3,352,169</p></td><td><p>£5,000</p></td><td><p><strong>£3,619,169</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p>£219,000</p></td><td><p>£2,744,545</p></td><td><p>£792,827</p></td><td><p><strong>£3,756,372</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p>£110,000</p></td><td><p>£1,444,270</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p><strong>£1,554,270</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p>£0</p><